HEADWORD: Angio-
<hw>An"gi*o-</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧n"j⟦icr⟧*⟦osl⟧-)</pr>. <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'aggei^on</grk> vessel receptacle.]</ety> <def>A prefix, or
combining form, in numerous compounds, usually relating to seed or blood
vessels, or to something contained in, or covered by, a
vessel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

